    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-09-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-09-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="396"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d396">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Foster</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Dupuy de Lôme</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-09-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 26, 1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 15th instant, and in reply to state that I have been informed
                    by the Acting Secretary of the Navy, in a letter dated the 23d instant, that
                    Rear-Admiral A. E. K. Benham, U. S. Navy, has been ordered to proceed to Cadiz,
                    Spain, with the United States flagship <hi rend="italic">Newark</hi>, by the 8th
                    of October next, and to accompany the Queen Regent of Spain when she leaves that
                    port for Huelva to dedicate the Columbus monument at that city.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John W. Foster.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
